    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>tofu</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Grate the<strong> tofu</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>cornflour </strong>and <strong>grated tofu</strong> in a bowl</p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>coated</strong> <strong>tofu</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-bulgogi-tofu-with-cauliflower-rice-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated</strong> <strong>tofu</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 10-15 min or until golden and crispy \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy tofu</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-bulgogi-tofu-with-cauliflower-rice-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 110ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[175ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[225ml]</span> cold water and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-bulgogi-tofu-with-cauliflower-rice-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your <strong>apple[s] </strong>(skin on) and discard the core[s]</p><p>Chop your <strong>sweet pea pods </strong>roughly</p><p>Meanwhile, wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>,<strong> </strong>then remove the <strong>outer leaves</strong> and pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Shred the<strong> inner core</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-bulgogi-tofu-with-cauliflower-rice-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>gochujang paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong>, <strong>gluten free soy sauce</strong> and most of your <strong>toasted sesame seeds </strong>(save some for garnish!) \u2013 this is your <strong>bulgogi-style sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-bulgogi-tofu-with-cauliflower-rice-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tofu is crispy, add the <strong>grated apple </strong>and cook for 5 min or until the apple has started to softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>bulgogi-style sauce </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant<strong> </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> Korean-style bulgogi tofu</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-bulgogi-tofu-with-cauliflower-rice-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is cooked, top the rice with the <strong>chopped sweet pea pods </strong>and put the lid back on for 2-3 min or until warmed through</p><p>Once warmed through, add the<strong> lettuce leaves</strong> and <strong>shredded core</strong> to a large bowl with the <strong>cooked rice & sweet pea pods</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> rice salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-bulgogi-tofu-with-cauliflower-rice-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Korean-style bulgogi tofu </strong>on top of the <strong>cauliflower rice salad</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved toasted sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
